Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan with the melted butter. Place eggs, milk and flour in a blender and whip until smooth. Pour into prepared pan. Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until golden. In a small saucepan, combine sugar, buttermilk, butter, corn syrup, baking soda; boil for 7 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Spoon over slices of pancake.